to the new camera in response to a user gesture.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/AnnotationViewExample":{"role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Add a custom annotation view","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/annotationviewexample","title":"Custom Annotation View","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/AnnotationViewExample","type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","type":"topic","title":"MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/ExampleStyles":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/examplestyles","abstract":[{"text":"The following styles are used in the examples:","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/ExampleStyles","title":"Styles in Examples","role":"article"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/BuildingLightExample":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/BuildingLightExample","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/buildinglightexample","abstract":[{"text":"Add a fill extrustion layer and adjust the light dynamically with a slider.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"article","title":"Fill Extrustion Layer"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolyline":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","type":"topic","title":"MLNPolyline","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolyline","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of two or more vertices,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the line segments that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"path along which something moves."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMapViewDelegate":{"kind":"symbol","title":"MLNMapViewDelegate","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a set of optional methods that you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can use to receive map-related update messages. Because many map operations","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"require the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","type":"reference"},{"text":" class to load data asynchronously, the map view calls","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"these methods to notify your application when specific operations complete. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"map view also uses these methods to request information about annotations","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"displayed on the map, such as the styles and interaction modes to apply to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"individual annotations.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapviewdelegate","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/or